reviews.text: What an amazing place. Food is outstanding and fairly priced. The staff are friendly and polite, the atmosphere is chilled and welcoming. Will definitely be back.

Really nice atmosphere. Excellent separation between the tables for covid. Really nice and helpful staff. Well cooked food breakfasts for 4 if us. Well presented food just sadly cold by the time we got it.
Great fish finger sandwiches. I go at least once a year just for that, please don't ever take it off the menu. Nice atmosphere and friendly service.

Food and drinks absolutely brilliant and reasonably priced. Rating is brought down by the poor advertisement of their booking policy. To clarify, you can book a table here despite what the website states.
Lovely alt venue. The cocktails are mad amazing. Fun desserts flavours and the staff are proper friendly

ChIJUSqRPcy9cEgRaKzsdRVLypg.name: Mr Gelato

reviews.text: Amazing waffle and ice cream(I had toffee) Good service and milkshakes are especially very delicious😋🥰
Amazing gelato.. Especially the freshly made mango gelato was inexplicably delicious. Warm hospitality

I went 14/11/2020 on Saturday with my friends. They came from far away just to have dessert. We ordered double chocolate cookie dough. It's uncooked. Also doesn't test at all. Iscream was disgusting. We throw everything in bin .Just waste of money. 😡😡

Ordered on ubereats, i had a message off the delivery driver to say he put it on my door step which he hadn't. So i contacted him and told him that there was no food on my doorstep and he told me it was there. When actually  he delivered it to a totally different address on a different road which I told him told him that there was no order on my door step and he put the phone down on me and havent heard from him since. I also contacted the shop to tell them what had happened  and the lady that was on the phone also put the phone down.
The people who work in this shop are rude& unprofessional and rubbish service.
will never be ordering from this place again.

We have ordered food twice from this place - the exact same thing both times. The first time was absolutely perfect! The second time which was yesterday was absolutely foul. We asked to take off bananas and it comes with strawberries instead we got a load iof raspberries and when we called to sort it out the manager was inceredbily rude and they hadn’t put strawberries because they had ‘ran out. I will not be ordering from here again simply because they could’ve sorted it out yet it took 3 hours and they did not plus i paid £15 for two waffles.
If I could post the pictures I would !!!
Do not order from here unless you wanted to be very disappointed!

Good coffee and amazing customer service found here! I sat in the seated area and witnessed some of the best cafe customer service ever. Many people were served very quickly and without any fuss or frustration on display. Groups of paramedics, patients, hospital staff and visitors were all involved in some form of conversation during order taking and whilst making collections.  I was really surprised for some reason. It was good to see.

One member of staff went above and beyond helping me with a phone issue I had and considering the circumstances of why I am at the QE today waiting she has no idea how much I value that gesture of kindness.

I feel that the management of this cafe should recognise and reward all the team members working today as they really are doing a great job and are a credit to Costa Coffee. They did not run out of friendliness, enthusiasm and energy in all the time I was here over 2 hours during peak times on a Saturday.

Thank you.

Staff aren’t as friendly as they used to be, service is slow even though enough people making drinks.
Service needs improving.

Used click and collect - the pick up point was not obvious to me so I queued up for 5 mins. When at the front of the queue the member of staff pointed in a direction and said I hadn’t looked hard enough.
Another staff member was nice enough to show me and apologised - hence the 2 stars.
Tried next day - they gave me a bacon bap instead of sausage - reduced to 1 star!
Service and coffee was good but the bacon roll was nasty im 99% sure the bacon in it is not meat don't ever have one

Very rude staff, black woman (didn't catch her name unfortunately) serving had a very bad attitude! Clearly had no training in how to speak to customers. I understand it might get busy and stressful but her customer service skills are appalling! I work in retail and am shocked. Not good service!

reviews.text: Can't rate this outlet highly enough,it gets extremely busy during lunchtimes but staff are efficient and always in great spirits. Super friendly. I've been out of term time also and the service level is fab then too, took my young daughter and our server was so nice to her, add some sparkly sprinkles to her drink which made her really happy. It's just those little extras that make for a great experience!
Best Costa I've been to, the Chinese guy makes the best drinks ever especially mocha :) everyone's nice and fast

I ordered a chai latte and it made me feel so sick I had to take a 5 min breather and tasted nothing like a latte. Overly sweet and no substance. Don’t recommend. To this day I’m still sitting I can’t even get up.
Good place to get you caffeine daily dose
Nice staff, pretty drab.
Nice little cafe at university of Birmingham library..If planning to get something for lunch here. Go before 12 am, or not many items will be left.
Had the chicken tikka panini and got severe stomach cramps and throwing up.
Pretty reasonable prices and nice atmosphere!
Great friendly staff, decently priced
Great little cafe by the Univeristy of Birmingham library, especially if you need a break!
Staff are very friendly. It's my morning treat. Hot chocolate and cake.
Nice small Starbucks counter with the same service as the big one. They always have a nice staff that serve you with smile even its busy sometimes. Have a good Cakes and sandwich options.
Worest Service!
Staff very rude
Coffee tasted like dish water and staff were rude

reviews.text: Lovely cafe with great coffee. Perfect for families with children
Lovely little cafe with a good range of toasties and cakes. You can paint pots in there, which is really nice. It has WiFi and is nice and bright and clean, ideal for students in the area.
So good  to  have a decent  coffee  again 😊😊
Lovely place, friendly staff, nice art on the walls :-)
Just called for a coffee and it was fine.

reviews.text:
Out all the stores I’ve been too across the West Midlands I have got to say that two of them are the best which is Harborne and Bearwood High Street.
The staff are professional and really friendly and I’ve always had consistent good service with a smile from both Serenity (Harborne) and Hadia (Bearwood). They are a credit to Greggs.
Excellent food and customer service.
Love this greggs. Staff are so lovely, friendly and welcoming. They always have enough food, even before they're about to close.

Every time I go into greggs in Harborne, the staff friendly ,fantastic, very helpful, always a smile.
And never make you feel like your a bother.
Thank you
The staff were so nice and made my day with their kindness! The store is clean and always has a good choice of food.

reviews.text: Great coffee and food, but staff could be friendlier, welcome customers, smile a bit and say goodbye.

I come almost everyday for a coffee, usually very nice staff and polite. It just one lady in there that I don’t know the name is very rude, not even sure why would you come to work with that attitude.
Great staff. Great coffee. Consistent quality.
Best coffee. Much stronger than Costa.
Great coffee shop, good changing facilities for babies. Good space for families or friend groups. Nice coffees. Good staff good atmosphere

reviews.text: Extremely loud heavy metal music playing. So off-putting. There was something floating in our black coffee and it had an acidic taste - couldn't finish it. Good service but the experience was not one I'd want to repeat.
Always a great place to visit. So much thought goes into their dishes and menu. Great visit as always.
Delicious! Really yummy food and great community vibe. Service was excellent (esp our super friendly server even on his first day). Will be going back asap :)
Lovely little cafe. Great hot chocolate. Lovely fresh cake. Really good music.
Interesting menu and delicious food. Fantastic and helpful staff. Great place for kids as well.

reviews.text: Great selection of M&S food, super clean and staff extremely friendly and always willing to help. Often find really good offers and reduced items too. Special thanks to Reed, often see him working here and he's always super friendly and helpful.
Good location, M&S food inside with a good selection.
Same as all other bp petrol stations very good fuel at a decent price
Lovely bp station clean and nice very compact and sell fresh coffee and fresh pastry ect and sell M&S food staff was very helpful and friendly
Repeat poor customer service

reviews.text: We had the most delicious food here, grilled peri chicken burger was perfect. The chips are absolutely to die for. Tried the Shisha for the first time too and it was a great experience. Couldn't fault anything at all, even the staff were amazing ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Shisha is good, coal gets changed regularly.
The vegan burger is amazing.
+1 for the spicy mango sauce

Really nice place for eating and chilling out.
Frequently visited for shishas.

Food: one of the best chicken burgers are made here (give the chicken fillet burger a try and you will understand why).
Great service food and drink. They even allow you to bring your own alcohol!
Excellent place to hang out. The peri wings are the best in Birmingham in my opinion. Kiran is a legend.

sausage roll undercooked, made us feel really unwell.
What can I say but yum,yum,yummy 😋
Great shop friendly staff

Has to be the only ever bakery that serves up cold sausages rolls ect.
Even the breakfast rolls are cold.
Who wants to eat cold sausages and  rubbery bacon its disqusting

The place was great, and the service it was quick because of the staff! Very good job.
Served on Monday 16th August by Paige. Very friendly and helpful. Happy customers.
I love costa but they didn't have any oat or almond milk today shame
We enjoyed coffees all round baristas great service loo clean what more could you want see you again soon.
I normally love Costa but they over charged me.  They told me they had over charged me and the Manager would sort it out.  He was apparently too busy to reimburse me and I was left over charged!

reviews.text:
One of the best bubble teas I've had. I had a black sugar milk tea with tapioca and 50% less sugar, but was still a little sweet for my taste.

The takeout cup is very strong, many others I've had have broken/exploded on a journey, but these cups are high quality.

Nice interior design. The eat-in spots are limited (only 3 people max, by the window),!perhaps still due to covid.

Fast service.
I will fight for Brown Sugar Boba Dirteas ... OMFG so good!
Simple no thrills bubble tea shop, the brown sugar milk tea with tapioca is great!
Very aesthetically pleasing decor, high quality cups but most important of all, delicious bubble tea!

I've found my new go-to bubble tea place! I tried the Brown Sugar Boba Milk Tea with Caramel Mousse. It was AMAZING- highly recommend if you like milky bubble tea! The lady who served me was really friendly. The drinks are also packaged and presented so well. Will visit again soon :)

reviews.text: Poor service. Two people behind the counter, each too busy doing their own thing to acknowledge me. A third person arrived and dealt with the customer in front of me. She then raised a forefinger as if to say 'with you in a minute' (no words were deemed necessary). All I wanted was a coffee but I left as I seemed to be an encumbrance rather than a customer.

Visited early on a Tuesday morning. Lady on the till was friendly, service was efficient. I ordered the breakfast deal; sausage in bread roll and a cappuccino and both were delicious. The bread was especially tasty
( foccacia style) being crispy on the outside with butter making the bread inside fluffy and gorgeous. The sausage was really tasty too, not overly seasoned and no gristle. Great music playing too! Overall,  a really pleasant experience.
Lovely place for breakfast, the sandwiches 9/10 👌🏻 but the pastries 3/10
Brilliant service, lovely food and drinks. Will go again and recommend to friends and family

Food and coffee was delicious but the wait was ridiculous. Advance warning that they were so far behind would have been appreciated. They seem to be trying to run it like a restaurant but it's a cafe and people want efficient service. Many others were coming to the counter to ask where their orders were. At tasty as it was I'll think twice before risk a 20 mins plus wait for a coffee and sandwich.

ChIJd_Hcw9W9cEgRvf2Hl1FWuuw.vicinity: Sainsbury's 19 Selly Oak Shopping Park, Aston Webb Boulevard, Birmingham

ChIJ_ab3fMy9cEgRm5dlNJXr43M.name: Cafe 55

reviews.text: I've been twice now and I'm definitely a fast fan. The staff are lovely, atmosphere is chill and the food more importantly is really good! Definitely happy to have stumbled upon this place

Tasty food. Had the fresh pineapple king prawn fried rice, delicious but only 5 prawns (I counted them)🤣
So, more prawns please.

Outrageous experience. I ordered the steak Noddle soup. The beef didn't taste fresh and it was mostly fat. The soup flavour was plain and overpowered with lemon flavour. I had to ask for pepper and coriander to lift the flavour. I mentioned it to the waiter which asked if I wanted to change it. I agreed. She went to speak with the chef, came back and offered to change the soup base and said that's how the steak comes. I asked to change it for a different dish,
She declined this. I asked to change it for the seafood Noddle soup. She said it was not fair with other clients because if one complains then they will have to do the same for everyone. I asked to speak to the manager. She said the manager is the chef and he doesn't speak well English and that's what he said. I was so upset as she initially offered to change it. I was hungry and my soup was already cold too with all this bad service. I told her to take the food away. A rip off and terrible customer service!
I've been here several times for the bubble tea. I highly recommend passionfruit bubble tea with lychee popping bubbles, so refreshing!!
Best Asian street food anywhere in Brum.
Lovely atmosphere and coffee, fabulous

reviews.text: Great staff who let me in as it was closing. Thanks it was really appreciated. Served quickly with my flat white. Quick chat, thanks etc and still had a smile on their faces after I can imagine a busy Saturday. 👏👏
Good location with outdoor seating and nice views of the campus. Staff friendly. Couldn't use my Starbucks card though as it is a franchise.
Delicious
Great coffee shop! Small but the staff are lovely.

Cleanest Starbucks in Birmingham. Friendly and courteous staff committed to delivering on the brand's service and cultural promises. I've been to Starbucks in many parts of the world and this ranks among the best. Great when busy. Welcoming when quiet.

Honestly what a beautiful cafe.

However, service at lunch time was super slow, with only one server which I found really odd. - despite there seeming to be members of staff available..

The person who served us was incredibly attentive to all customers though, which was so nice to see.

Beautiful setting, pretty good coffee, just speed up the orders during the lunch rush and you'd have 5 stars from me!
